post_text:
Class of 2020 Graduates,

Our celebration of graduates will take place outside on our property behind the playground on Wednesday, July 8 at 10:00 AM. Graduates need to arrive by 9:45 AM and report to the grassy area by the playground. You will receive further instructions at that time. If graduates are wearing their cap and gown, the tassel should hang to the left.

For the health and safety of all, wearing a face covering is mandatory.

Seating will not be provided. Please remind your family/guests to bring their own chair or blanket for sitting (you will be joining your family in the audience so remember a seat for you).

We hope to see you tomorrow!

post_text:
Yearbooks!

Online sales have ended.
If you would still like to purchase a yearbook, they can be purchased during STUDENT PICK-UP of materials for $25 - no cash or transfer of funds.
They can be picked up at the main office Monday - Friday 8:30AM to Noon. This includes pre paid yearbooks as well.
Checks should be made out to HAINESPORT STUDENTS ACTIVITIES FUND.
Yearbooks are still available on a first come first serve basis!

VIRTUAL YEARBOOK SIGNING IS AVAILABLE. Yearbooks tell the story. Students provide the commentary. Virtual yearbook signing is now available through Walsworth and Kudoboard!
Your students can make an online board now that their friends and the school community can sign with messages and photos, while staying six feet apart the whole time. It’s easy! All students have to do is text, email or share their link on social media with their friends. When they’re done, they will save their board as a hi-res JPEG and can keep it digitally or print to place inside the yearbook. See the flyers below!

Any questions? Reach out to Mrs. Orfe
orfe@hainesport.k12.nj.us

post_text:
Today would have been our 2020 graduates’ final concert at Hainesport School. We are extremely proud of their dedication, passion and commitment to the music program. Many of our graduates began participating in choir and band in 4th and 5th grade before continuing their love for music through middle school.

Over the years, students have performed annual winter and spring concerts, challenged themselves in regional honors band and choir festivals, participated in the Hainesport Township tree lighting ceremony, and brought smiles to senior citizens at Brandywine Living Center. Last year our students were awarded a “Superior" rating at Elizabethtown College for their performance at the annual High Note Festival.

Mrs. Cahill and Mrs. Rothkopf wish the graduating students success in high school and hope they continue their passion for music in the years to come!

Some videos to come! ☺️

post_text: Mr. Mark Love of Engineers Teaching Algebra recently presented a workshop to our eighth grade Algebra I students. To promote STEM education, students were engaged in inquiry-based learning as they designed safe traffic patterns in three- and four-way intersections. Students were tasked with using algebraic reasoning to develop a safe and efficient phasing plan for the traffic light signals to address the volume of traffic in 90-second cycles. Throughout the presentation, students were actively engaged in problem-solving and eager to share their thoughts and plans with Mr. Love. Great job! #hawksconnect

post_text:
If your child will be five years of age by October 1, 2020, please download and print the Kindergarten Registration Packet, and call the Special Services Office at 609-518-9081 to schedule an appointment to register. Appointments are available on Monday, March 30th and Tuesday, March 31st in fifteen minute increments.

To find the registration packet, go to our website: http://www.hainesport.k12.nj.us/ , scroll down to our Announcements, and click on Kindergarten Registration 2020-2021!

Please be sure to fill out all pages of the registration packet, paying special attention to the supporting documents required, and bring all necessary documents to your registration appointment. Your child is not required to attend the registration appointment. We look forward to welcoming your family to Hainesport Township School! #classof2033 #hawksconnect

post_text:
For School Violence Awareness Week, Detective Joseph Santamaria, from the NJ State Police came out to do a presentation with our 6th, 7th, and 8th graders! The focus of the assembly was to bring awareness to Internet Safety. Topics such as cyberbullying, online privacy, inappropriate content, and online predators were discussed with our students. Thank you Det. Santamaria for providing our students with lots of information on Internet Safety!

If you are interested in the information given to our students, there will be a parent presentation on November 12th from 7:00-8:00 covering the the same Internet Safety topics and more! This is a parent-only presentation, children will not be permitted to attend.

#schoolviolenceawarenessweek #hawksconnect

Due to inclement weather, Hainesport Township School will have a 2 HOUR DELAY on Friday. March 1, 2019.

In response to the 2 Hour Delayed opening on Friday, March 1st, Hainesport Township School Read Across America activities will be rescheduled for a date to be determined in the near future. More information to follow. For Friday, March 1st, participating students can still wear Pajamas, as well as bring in their completed Bingo Boards. The assembly portion of the day will continue as planned. We apologize for any inconvenience and thank you for your understanding.

post_text: Hainesport Township School District is achieving Eco-Excellent goals! Competing against teams across the world, Hainesport Township School came in 6th place for the October Eco-Challenge! In conjunction with this awesome initiative Hainesport Township middle school students Paige Iovine, Violet Bolyard, Leah Howe, Ty Martin, Brian Flanders, Jake Bartletta, & Matt Hammell had the opportunity to present to the Hainesport Board of Education the importance and knowledge gained from being dedicated to the Eco-Challenge, as well as share the successful Eco-Friendly materials and packaging they created in Mr. Stipa’s class! #hawksconnect #ecochallenge #loveourearth #biodegradable

Check out 6th Grade student Brian Flanders helping 2nd Grade students Isabella Mancuso and Giovanni Leont, from Ms. Anderson's class, make a very important morning announcement!

The Great Bedtime pajama Drive has come to an end. The pajamas have been sorted and counted! Our school collected a total of 126 pajamas!! Thank you to everyone that gave pajamas and supported this cause. Because of you, 126 children in need will receive a new pair of pajamas and a new book during this holiday season.

2nd Grade students from Ms. Anderson's class sorted the pajamas by size, labeled the different size groups with index cards, compiled the information and input the data into google sheets. #HAWKSconnect #Scholastic #PajamaProgram #kidshelpingkids

Hainesport Township School District added 20 new photos.
November 13, 2018 at 5:07 PM ·

Cup challenge with Mrs. Rodriguez & Mrs. Ellis's class!
Students' goal is to work together using provided materials to achieve success at each station.
* Remember to be patient and kind while persevering to obtain each goal!
Step 1- Practice working together to lift a solo cup using your individual strings that are attached to your group rubber band
Step 2- (set a goal): Begin with a 3 cup pyramid and build on your pyramid as you feel more comfortable.
Overall goal- to make the tallest, most sturdy formation!
